{"body": "Thank you for the pull request.\r\n\r\nI don't think `+=` is a supported API for two reasons:\r\n\r\n1. You don't expect that `+=` mutates the receiver object and the current implementation does that.\r\n1. This will allow `comments = post.comments + comment` and I think we don't want this.\r\n\r\nThe right thing to do is to use one of the documented method: `<<`, `push` or `append`.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/23241147", "created_at": "2013-08-26T02:35:56Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/12019#issuecomment-23241147", "updated_at": "2013-08-26T02:35:56Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 12019, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/rafaelfranca", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2c7b84fa30f0cea96a90729afe2970a0.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/received_events", "gravatar_id": "0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "rafaelfranca", "type": "User", "id": 47848, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523babccbd3543c151018e97"}, "id": 23241147, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/12019"}
